the simulator right now with the

00:29:57.946 --> 00:29:59.056 A:middle
Accessibility Inspector.

00:29:59.056 --> 00:30:00.736 A:middle
And I found the Accessibility

00:30:00.736 --> 00:30:02.116 A:middle
Inspector in Xcode under

00:30:02.116 --> 00:30:03.086 A:middle
Developer Tools.

00:30:03.206 --> 00:30:04.496 A:middle
And there's a lot you can do

00:30:04.496 --> 00:30:04.746 A:middle
here.

00:30:04.746 --> 00:30:05.686 A:middle
And I'm not really going to go

00:30:05.686 --> 00:30:06.806 A:middle
into it because there's a really

00:30:06.806 --> 00:30:07.986 A:middle
great talk in it last year.

00:30:08.496 --> 00:30:09.936 A:middle
But over here you can inspect

00:30:09.936 --> 00:30:10.396 A:middle
your app.

00:30:10.396 --> 00:30:11.396 A:middle
And so, it will tell you what

00:30:11.396 --> 00:30:12.396 A:middle
different accessibility

00:30:12.396 --> 00:30:13.936 A:middle
information it can get about the

00:30:13.936 --> 00:30:15.036 A:middle
things in your app.

00:30:15.436 --> 00:30:16.856 A:middle
Or you could run an audit which

00:30:16.856 --> 00:30:18.036 A:middle
is really helpful, because it

00:30:18.036 --> 00:30:18.986 A:middle
will just highlight some

00:30:18.986 --> 00:30:20.396 A:middle
different accessibility bugs you

00:30:20.396 --> 00:30:21.436 A:middle
might have in your game.

00:30:22.246 --> 00:30:23.146 A:middle
But, today we're going to look

00:30:23.146 --> 00:30:23.956 A:middle
at the settings tab.

00:30:23.956 --> 00:30:26.116 A:middle
And this is really cool, because

00:30:26.116 --> 00:30:27.606 A:middle
it lets you test different

00:30:27.786 --> 00:30:29.186 A:middle
accessibility settings without

00:30:29.186 --> 00:30:29.966 A:middle
leaving your game.

00:30:30.296 --> 00:30:31.296 A:middle
And I'm just doing this on the

00:30:31.296 --> 00:30:33.176 A:middle
simulator, but up here if you

00:30:33.176 --> 00:30:34.326 A:middle
have your phone plugged in, you

00:30:34.326 --> 00:30:36.726 A:middle
can actually pick your phone too

00:30:37.006 --> 00:30:38.346 A:middle
and so you could do it on device

00:30:38.346 --> 00:30:39.726 A:middle
and that way you don't have to

00:30:39.726 --> 00:30:41.496 A:middle
leave your game and like go into

00:30:41.496 --> 00:30:42.356 A:middle
settings and go back.

00:30:42.396 --> 00:30:43.126 A:middle
So, it's really handy.

00:30:43.776 --> 00:30:45.666 A:middle
So, one that we did was reduce

00:30:45.666 --> 00:30:46.546 A:middle
transparency.

00:30:46.586 --> 00:30:47.506 A:middle
And for that we just did a

00:30:47.506 --> 00:30:49.146 A:middle
simple black background to make

00:30:49.146 --> 00:30:50.536 A:middle
the gameboard really stand out.

00:30:51.736 --> 00:30:53.246 A:middle
We also supported different font

00:30:53.246 --> 00:30:54.786 A:middle
sizes for dynamic type.

00:30:54.786 --> 00:30:56.066 A:middle
So, there's a slider here and I

00:30:56.066 --> 00:30:57.616 A:middle
can just make the fonts bigger

00:30:57.616 --> 00:30:58.276 A:middle
or smaller.

00:30:59.286 --> 00:31:00.966 A:middle
And the next one is invert

00:31:00.966 --> 00:31:01.446 A:middle
colors.

00:31:01.446 --> 00:31:03.466 A:middle
And to know why we implemented

00:31:03.466 --> 00:31:04.956 A:middle
it the way we did, you have to

00:31:04.956 --> 00:31:06.326 A:middle
know a little bit about how it's

00:31:06.326 --> 00:31:06.846 A:middle
used.

00:31:07.286 --> 00:31:09.016 A:middle
So, invert colors is used by

00:31:09.116 --> 00:31:10.506 A:middle
players who have difficulty

00:31:10.506 --> 00:31:12.226 A:middle
reading dark text on a light

00:31:12.276 --> 00:31:13.036 A:middle
background because the

00:31:13.036 --> 00:31:14.326 A:middle
brightness of the background

00:31:14.406 --> 00:31:15.606 A:middle
interferes with their vision.

00:31:15.976 --> 00:31:17.486 A:middle
So, they'll use invert colors,

00:31:17.486 --> 00:31:18.916 A:middle
to make that light text on a

00:31:18.916 --> 00:31:20.026 A:middle
dark background instead.

00:31:20.966 --> 00:31:22.186 A:middle
Since our game is already like

00:31:22.256 --> 00:31:23.946 A:middle
that, we used the accessibility

00:31:23.946 --> 00:31:25.496 A:middle
API to tell it not to invert

00:31:25.496 --> 00:31:26.656 A:middle
colors for this screen.

00:31:27.066 --> 00:31:28.636 A:middle
So, when I do invert colors,

00:31:29.046 --> 00:31:30.096 A:middle
nothing happens.

00:31:30.256 --> 00:31:31.646 A:middle
But if I go to like settings,

00:31:31.646 --> 00:31:33.636 A:middle
which is normally white, it's

00:31:33.636 --> 00:31:34.126 A:middle
all black.

00:31:34.396 --> 00:31:36.626 A:middle
And then if I uncheck it, it

00:31:36.626 --> 00:31:38.006 A:middle
goes back to white.

00:31:38.596 --> 00:31:40.056 A:middle
So, we have a lot of different

00:31:40.056 --> 00:31:41.306 A:middle
settings here in this game that

00:31:41.706 --> 00:31:43.046 A:middle
we added for accessibility

00:31:43.046 --> 00:31:43.466 A:middle
reasons.

00:31:43.466 --> 00:31:44.786 A:middle
So, let's check that out as

00:31:44.786 --> 00:31:45.036 A:middle
well.

00:31:46.496 --> 00:31:48.786 A:middle
So, here's my Four in a Row app.

00:31:48.786 --> 00:31:50.136 A:middle
I can just tap on a column to

00:31:50.136 --> 00:31:50.796 A:middle
make a move.

00:31:51.896 --> 00:31:53.686 A:middle
But more exciting than the game

00:31:53.686 --> 00:31:54.846 A:middle
is the settings.

00:31:55.116 --> 00:31:56.626 A:middle
And we have a lot here.

00:31:57.016 --> 00:31:58.216 A:middle
So, first is volume.

00:31:58.516 --> 00:32:00.296 A:middle
We added different sliders for

00:32:00.296 --> 00:32:01.646 A:middle
the speech and the sound effects

00:32:01.646 --> 00:32:03.236 A:middle
because people who are hard of

00:32:03.306 --> 00:32:05.516 A:middle
hearing might want to emphasize

00:32:05.516 --> 00:32:06.586 A:middle
the speech over the sound

00:32:06.586 --> 00:32:06.956 A:middle
effects.

00:32:07.556 --> 00:32:08.716 A:middle
So, we could turn down the sound

00:32:08.716 --> 00:32:08.976 A:middle
effects.

00:32:11.536 --> 00:32:13.536 A:middle
We also have captions.

00:32:13.536 --> 00:32:14.956 A:middle
And so, those are just going

00:32:14.956 --> 00:32:16.306 A:middle
directly from the settings for

00:32:16.306 --> 00:32:16.926 A:middle
your phone.

00:32:17.526 --> 00:32:18.586 A:middle
And we have Differentiate

00:32:18.586 --> 00:32:19.256 A:middle
Without Color.

00:32:19.256 --> 00:32:21.626 A:middle
And if you noticed before, right

00:32:21.626 --> 00:32:22.856 A:middle
now it's all circles.

00:32:23.316 --> 00:32:24.766 A:middle
But when I turn on Differentiate

00:32:24.766 --> 00:32:27.266 A:middle
Without Colors, we made it so

00:32:27.266 --> 00:32:28.616 A:middle
now it's circles and triangles.

00:32:28.616 --> 00:32:30.216 A:middle
So, it's easier to tell apart

00:32:30.816 --> 00:32:31.716 A:middle
the different players.

00:32:32.316 --> 00:32:34.526 A:middle
So, we have a lot of other

00:32:34.626 --> 00:32:35.946 A:middle
settings here, but the one I

00:32:35.946 --> 00:32:38.016 A:middle
wanted to focus on was timing.

00:32:39.046 --> 00:32:40.916 A:middle
We added a Turn Time slider

00:32:40.916 --> 00:32:42.336 A:middle
which is great because that

00:32:42.336 --> 00:32:44.076 A:middle
gives players who have trouble

00:32:44.076 --> 00:32:45.096 A:middle
coming up their next move or

00:32:45.096 --> 00:32:46.646 A:middle
difficulty moving that quickly

00:32:46.696 --> 00:32:48.016 A:middle
some extra time to make their

00:32:48.016 --> 00:32:48.426 A:middle
move.

00:32:49.006 --> 00:32:49.956 A:middle
But for now, I'm going to turn

00:32:49.956 --> 00:32:51.076 A:middle
off the timed mode because I'm

00:32:51.076 --> 00:32:52.066 A:middle
going to be testing this out

