&gt;&gt; Move empty image, empty

00:33:28.656 --> 00:33:30.716 A:middle
image, empty image.

00:33:32.106 --> 00:33:34.166 A:middle
Winner, four question marks.

00:33:34.166 --> 00:33:35.956 A:middle
Actions of player B, image.

00:33:35.956 --> 00:33:37.186 A:middle
Player B image.

00:33:37.966 --> 00:33:41.396 A:middle
Actions available.

00:33:41.616 --> 00:33:43.806 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So, I can move to everything.

00:33:43.806 --> 00:33:45.426 A:middle
It's labelled, it's accessible,

00:33:45.426 --> 00:33:46.746 A:middle
but when I was testing this out

00:33:46.746 --> 00:33:48.566 A:middle
earlier in VoiceOver, I found it

00:33:48.566 --> 00:33:49.776 A:middle
just wasn't a really fun

00:33:49.776 --> 00:33:50.326 A:middle
experience.

00:33:50.326 --> 00:33:52.356 A:middle
It was too hard to move through

00:33:52.356 --> 00:33:53.766 A:middle
all the different slots on the

00:33:53.766 --> 00:33:55.856 A:middle
gameboard, keep track in your

00:33:55.856 --> 00:33:56.936 A:middle
head of which ones were filled

00:33:56.936 --> 00:33:57.966 A:middle
and which weren't and come up

00:33:57.966 --> 00:33:59.556 A:middle
with what your next move should

00:33:59.556 --> 00:33:59.836 A:middle
be.

00:34:00.646 --> 00:34:02.116 A:middle
So, I used something in the

00:34:02.116 --> 00:34:03.636 A:middle
accessibility API called the

00:34:03.636 --> 00:34:05.216 A:middle
Custom Action to improve that

00:34:05.216 --> 00:34:05.956 A:middle
experience.

00:34:06.346 --> 00:34:07.846 A:middle
I added an action that switches

00:34:07.846 --> 00:34:09.306 A:middle
you from moving by cell to

00:34:09.306 --> 00:34:10.156 A:middle
moving by column.

00:34:10.666 --> 00:34:12.086 A:middle
Let's do that.

00:34:13.356 --> 00:34:16.056 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Move by cell, move by column.

00:34:16.786 --> 00:34:20.606 A:middle
Column 3, 4 empty cells, 2

00:34:20.606 --> 00:34:21.656 A:middle
player A tokens.

00:34:22.776 --> 00:34:24.256 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So, that way VoiceOver can

00:34:24.256 --> 00:34:25.606 A:middle
move via column instead of by

00:34:25.606 --> 00:34:27.376 A:middle
cell and that makes it a lot

00:34:27.376 --> 00:34:28.636 A:middle
easier for me to just get a

00:34:28.636 --> 00:34:30.056 A:middle
sense of what the gameboard is

00:34:30.056 --> 00:34:30.123 A:middle
in.

00:34:30.123 --> 00:34:32.266 A:middle
And that technique I used for

00:34:32.266 --> 00:34:34.216 A:middle
making it move by column instead

00:34:34.216 --> 00:34:35.516 A:middle
of by cell was also really

00:34:35.516 --> 00:34:36.636 A:middle
helpful for Switch Control.

00:34:36.636 --> 00:34:37.686 A:middle
So, let me show you that.

00:34:37.686 --> 00:34:39.276 A:middle
I'm going to turn off VoiceOver

00:34:39.276 --> 00:34:40.306 A:middle
and switch over to Switch

00:34:40.306 --> 00:34:40.676 A:middle
Control.

00:34:41.836 --> 00:34:43.686 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Alert. Accessibility list

00:34:43.686 --> 00:34:44.966 A:middle
control button.

00:34:45.146 --> 00:34:45.976 A:middle
VoiceOver off.

00:34:48.426 --> 00:34:50.406 A:middle
&gt;&gt; OK, so now I have Switch

00:34:50.406 --> 00:34:51.846 A:middle
Control on and I have my switch

00:34:51.846 --> 00:34:52.166 A:middle
here.

00:34:52.776 --> 00:34:54.816 A:middle
And Switch Control is scanning

00:34:54.816 --> 00:34:57.096 A:middle
all the things, I'm sorry.

00:34:57.126 --> 00:34:58.316 A:middle
Switch Control is scanning all

00:34:58.316 --> 00:34:59.876 A:middle
the items on the screen and so

00:34:59.876 --> 00:35:02.396 A:middle
when I go into the gameboard,

00:35:02.876 --> 00:35:04.236 A:middle
it's going to, before it was

00:35:04.236 --> 00:35:06.236 A:middle
going by cell, and it was super

00:35:06.236 --> 00:35:07.826 A:middle
tedious to try to wait for it to

00:35:07.826 --> 00:35:09.536 A:middle
go through each cell to get to

00:35:09.536 --> 00:35:10.556 A:middle
the one that I wanted.

00:35:11.026 --> 00:35:12.126 A:middle
But now, when I go into the

00:35:12.126 --> 00:35:14.556 A:middle
gameboard, it's going by column

00:35:14.556 --> 00:35:15.726 A:middle
instead of by cell, which it did

00:35:15.726 --> 00:35:16.876 A:middle
originally, and so I was able to

00:35:16.876 --> 00:35:18.516 A:middle
use accessibility API to change

00:35:18.516 --> 00:35:19.566 A:middle
that experience to make it

00:35:19.566 --> 00:35:19.866 A:middle
better.

00:35:20.316 --> 00:35:21.696 A:middle
So now I can just press my

00:35:21.696 --> 00:35:24.246 A:middle
switch and make my move.

00:35:26.536 --> 00:35:28.196 A:middle
So, let me show you some other

00:35:28.256 --> 00:35:29.486 A:middle
things that we did.

00:35:29.796 --> 00:35:30.976 A:middle
Let me turn off Switch Control.

00:35:33.826 --> 00:35:34.986 A:middle
And right now, if you're

00:35:34.986 --> 00:35:36.986 A:middle
noticing I have my screen setup

00:35:36.986 --> 00:35:38.036 A:middle
to be a switch too.

00:35:38.036 --> 00:35:40.056 A:middle
And that's an awesome option for

00:35:40.056 --> 00:35:41.086 A:middle
testing, because that way you

00:35:41.086 --> 00:35:42.436 A:middle
don't need to set up a switch.

00:35:42.516 --> 00:35:44.716 A:middle
So, you're just, your phone

00:35:44.716 --> 00:35:45.716 A:middle
works as a switch.

00:35:46.396 --> 00:35:48.446 A:middle
Okay, so we also made it work

00:35:48.446 --> 00:35:49.086 A:middle
with a keyboard.

00:35:49.086 --> 00:35:50.226 A:middle
And so, I mentioned earlier for

00:35:50.226 --> 00:35:51.406 A:middle
that, you needed to do a

00:35:51.406 --> 00:35:53.356 A:middle
selection mechanism, so that way

00:35:53.356 --> 00:35:55.586 A:middle
when I hit the arrow keys, I can

00:35:55.586 --> 00:35:57.256 A:middle
move by column, and then just

00:35:57.256 --> 00:35:59.246 A:middle
press space to make my move.

00:36:00.996 --> 00:36:03.736 A:middle
So, providing these options for

00:36:03.736 --> 00:36:04.726 A:middle
these different assistive

00:36:04.726 --> 00:36:06.036 A:middle
technologies really broadens

00:36:06.036 --> 00:36:06.836 A:middle
into my audience.

00:36:06.836 --> 00:36:07.956 A:middle
It means a lot more people will

00:36:07.956 --> 00:36:09.246 A:middle
be able to play our game.

00:36:09.786 --> 00:36:12.576 A:middle
We were able to make a lot of

00:36:12.576 --> 00:36:13.766 A:middle
improvements to our game by

00:36:13.766 --> 00:36:14.896 A:middle
testing it out with different

00:36:14.896 --> 00:36:16.136 A:middle
assistive technologies and

00:36:16.136 --> 00:36:17.496 A:middle
accessibility settings.

00:36:18.216 --> 00:36:19.116 A:middle
When you're doing this, it can

00:36:19.116 --> 00:36:20.686 A:middle
be easy to fall into the trap of

00:36:20.686 --> 00:36:22.116 A:middle
following the letter of the law,

00:36:22.116 --> 00:36:23.136 A:middle
but not the spirit.

00:36:23.526 --> 00:36:25.186 A:middle
As well as being accessible, you

00:36:25.186 --> 00:36:26.466 A:middle
want your game to be fun to play

00:36:26.466 --> 00:36:27.186 A:middle
for everyone.

00:36:28.106 --> 00:36:29.826 A:middle
The accessibility API offers a

00:36:29.826 --> 00:36:31.256 A:middle
lot of great tools for improving

00:36:31.256 --> 00:36:32.306 A:middle
that experience.

00:36:33.696 --> 00:36:35.036 A:middle
Now, you may be thinking about

00:36:35.036 --> 00:36:36.606 A:middle
your own app and how you can get

00:36:36.696 --> 00:36:38.056 A:middle
started making it accessible.

00:36:38.666 --> 00:36:39.926 A:middle
The three things you can do the

00:36:39.926 --> 00:36:41.556 A:middle
minute you walk out of here are

00:36:41.556 --> 00:36:43.696 A:middle
to audit your app, test it out

00:36:43.696 --> 00:36:44.756 A:middle
with different accessibility

00:36:44.756 --> 00:36:46.746 A:middle
settings, and most importantly,

00:36:46.856 --> 00:36:48.196 A:middle
talk to assistive technology

00:36:48.196 --> 00:36:48.886 A:middle
users.

00:36:49.286 --> 00:36:52.956 A:middle
So, we already mentioned this

00:36:53.016 --> 00:36:53.986 A:middle
talk a little bit, but it's

00:36:53.986 --> 00:36:54.556 A:middle
really good.

00:36:54.556 --> 00:36:55.456 A:middle
So, you can learn more about

00:36:55.456 --> 00:36:56.766 A:middle
both auditing your app and

00:36:56.766 --> 00:36:57.906 A:middle
testing it with accessibility

00:36:57.906 --> 00:36:59.746 A:middle
settings and Auditing your Apps

00:36:59.746 --> 00:37:01.296 A:middle
for Accessibility talk from last

00:37:01.296 --> 00:37:01.466 A:middle
year.

00:37:02.036 --> 00:37:04.916 A:middle
It's really important to test

00:37:04.916 --> 00:37:06.256 A:middle
out your game with assistive

00:37:06.256 --> 00:37:07.646 A:middle
technologies, but you should

00:37:07.646 --> 00:37:09.126 A:middle
also try to talk to the users

00:37:09.126 --> 00:37:10.186 A:middle
who use them every day.

00:37:10.806 --> 00:37:11.696 A:middle
They'll have a firsthand

00:37:11.696 --> 00:37:13.036 A:middle
experience of what separates a

00:37:13.036 --> 00:37:14.446 A:middle
good experience from a great

00:37:14.446 --> 00:37:14.876 A:middle
experience.

00:37:14.876 --> 00:37:16.316 A:middle
And they'll probably have a lot

00:37:16.316 --> 00:37:17.646 A:middle
of ideas for how you can make

00:37:17.646 --> 00:37:18.836 A:middle
your game more accessible.

00:37:19.456 --> 00:37:20.366 A:middle
You can connect with

00:37:20.366 --> 00:37:21.666 A:middle
accessibility users and

00:37:21.666 --> 00:37:23.136 A:middle
developers at our get-together

00:37:23.136 --> 00:37:23.456 A:middle
tonight.

00:37:24.696 --> 00:37:25.616 A:middle
Designing your game for

00:37:25.616 --> 00:37:27.296 A:middle
accessibility really means more

00:37:27.296 --> 00:37:28.966 A:middle
people can enjoy it.

00:37:29.716 --> 00:37:31.026 A:middle
When you're designing for

00:37:31.026 --> 00:37:32.336 A:middle
accessibility think about how

00:37:32.336 --> 00:37:33.616 A:middle
accessibility is really a

00:37:33.616 --> 00:37:34.206 A:middle
spectrum.

00:37:34.386 --> 00:37:35.576 A:middle
So, you want to create these

00:37:35.636 --> 00:37:37.326 A:middle
different great experiences so

00:37:37.496 --> 00:37:38.966 A:middle
each player can find out their

00:37:38.966 --> 00:37:39.716 A:middle
own perfect fit.

00:37:39.716 --> 00:37:42.606 A:middle
At the end of the day, your game

00:37:42.606 --> 00:37:43.876 A:middle
will be stronger and richer,

00:37:43.876 --> 00:37:45.156 A:middle
because designing for

00:37:45.156 --> 00:37:46.436 A:middle
accessibility is really

00:37:46.436 --> 00:37:47.616 A:middle
designing for everyone.

